unspeakable horrors lie within this code block; fortunately for you, you're not responsible for any of them. This code was in dire need of a re-write long before you touched it :)
- yoda style for `>=` comparisons is not clever or useful, it's just deliberate obfuscation
- use `std::unique_ptr<char[]>` instead of manually calling `delete[]`

those nested `if` branches give me internal bleedings just from looking at them... how about you put that code block into its own `std::string get_snd_fname(int id)` function that uses a for-each loop similar to this pseudocode:

